@remy727 , yes. I added the new scope to `config/initializers/shopify_app.rb`.  

Then, change`config.reauth_on_access_scope_changes = false`. This should prevent existing users from having to refresh their scope. New users will get the full scope.

If an existing user needs to refresh their scope, you can create a new process for that. We ended up overwriting the logic in`ShopAccessScopesVerification#login_on_scope_changes` using another module, so we can control when to redirect to login. Instead of `if scope_mismatch?` we check for other conditions, like the scope column being empty, for example.
